Description: Sherd of shoulder of pottery closed vessel, probably amphora, close to handle attachment; micaceous brick-red clay; thin cream slip. Rather thin wall for an amphora. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 406)

Johnston 2006b / The Delta: From Gamma to Zeta (p.28 Table 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.761)
